>>37013838
There's basically three types of edible fruit (don't you fuck with me botanists, you know what I mean) in this world, those evolved for mammals, those evolved for birds, and those evolved for insects. Most of the fruits that are poisonous or try to repel us aren't so for birds, the main reason they want to get rid of mammals is due to mastication and the stronger stomach acids they have. Birds just swallow them whole and can't digest the seed or its protective kernel, and so don't get poisoned. Not so for mammals. Most mammal-targeting fruit tends to have extra hardy, large, or protected seeds that can survive the mammals' tough digestive tract or more effectively dissuade them from eating it. Examples include things like apples, pears, avocados, peaches etc. Most bird-targeting fruit is much smaller so they can effectively swallow it. Insect-targeting fruit is all over the place in strategy, but tend to be very highly specialized. The most well-known insect-targeting fruit is the fig, which has evolved a symbiotic relationship with wasps where they pollinate it to cause seeds to germinate and in turn lay their eggs in specialized chambers that protect and feed the larva.

Anyway peppers fucked all this up because humans are literally insane and enjoy food that burns and hurts, so their mammal-repelling strategy fails for us.
